@@eThe Cinderteeth: Seismic Risk Assessment@@N

@@yHazard Registry, Bureau of Route Stability@@N
@@dFiled under: Geological Threat, Conclave Liability, Trade Disruption@@N

The Cinderteeth Mountains are not Midgaard's territory. They are
Midgaard's @@rproblem@@N. Every tremor in that volcanic arc translates
into route instability, convoy losses, and emergency requisitions
drawn against the city's grain reserves.

The @@rAsh Winters@@N proved this. Eruptions sent ash clouds across the
continent, contaminating wells, poisoning the Great Northern Forest's
streams, devastating @@yKowloon's@@N delta. Our ledgers from those years
are stained with emergency ink -- @@dred-bordered entries@@N marking crisis
expenditures that nearly bankrupted the Passage Tithe. The Bureau of
Route Stability was founded in the aftermath.

The @@yHazard Doctrine@@N maintained by the range's route houses is, to
our assessment, @@eentirely sensible@@N. The @@WSilent Bell Protocol@@N mirrors
our own emergency lamp procedures. The @@rDouble-water doctrine@@N is the
kind of hard-won operational law our @@WOath of the Kept Record@@N was
designed to preserve. We recognize institutional rigor even where our
jurisdiction does not reach.

What we cannot forgive is the @@WSpirebound Conclave@@N.

Our ledgers contain the evidence. @@dArchive drawer seven, requisition
volume nineteen@@N: entries recording payment for condemned debtors
transferred to the mountain academy. @@d"Forty iron bars and six
condemned debtors"@@N -- our citizens, sent to isolation that made
research possible and @@raccountability impossible@@N. We enabled the
Conclave with bodies and iron. When it collapsed, leaving unretrieved
@@lresonance crystals@@N at fault intersections, we bore partial
responsibility for every sympathetic tremor since.

The @@rAsh Cult@@N that claims eruptions pronounce divine verdict against
civic corruption is, our Bureau notes with discomfort, not entirely
wrong about the corruption -- only about the divinity.

Six subregions in our threat assessments: the @@rEmber Crown@@N rated
impassable, the @@dBellspine@@N rated severe-disorientation, the
@@WChalkwind Saddles@@N rated viable-with-escort, the @@yGlasswash Fans@@N
rated extractable, the @@gBlackstep Footholds@@N where our jurisdiction
technically begins, and the @@lWestern Fold@@N formally @@ddesignated:
do not approach without tribunal authorization@@N.

The mountains remind us that seismic risk is also @@rmoral risk@@N. What
the city sent into those peaks has not finished returning.
